===============================================================================
                                 M A G I C I U M
===============================================================================
A hybrid C++ & WebKitGTK image utility. Native performance, minimalist overhead.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. QUICK START
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Make sure you install the [Prerequisites] first.

[Option A: Automated Installation (Recommended)]
  git clone https://github.com/Alepherite/magicium.git
  cd magicium
  chmod +x install.sh
  ./install.sh

[Option B: Manual Compilation]
  git clone https://github.com/Alepherite/magicium.git
  cd magicium
  make
  build/magicium

[Update]
  - Option A (Global): Run 'magicium-update' from anywhere.
  - Option B (Source): Run './update.sh' from inside the repository folder.

[Uninstall]
  - Option A (Global): Run 'magicium-uninstall' from anywhere.
  - Option B (Source): Run './uninstall.sh' from inside the repository folder.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. PREREQUISITES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install development libraries based on your Linux distribution:

[Debian / Ubuntu / Linux Mint]
  sudo apt install build-essential libgtk-3-dev libwebkit2gtk-4.1-dev \
                   imagemagick libnotify-bin

[Fedora / RHEL]
  sudo dnf install gcc-c++ make gtk3-devel webkit2gtk4.1-devel \
                   ImageMagick libnotify

[Arch Linux / CachyOS / Manjaro]
  sudo pacman -S base-devel gtk3 webkit2gtk-4.1 imagemagick libnotify

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. FEATURES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Hybrid Architecture: HTML5/JS/CSS frontend sitting directly on a compiled
  C++ core.
* Zero Base64 Overhead: Passes absolute file paths straight to the native
  'magick' binary.
* Asynchronous Processing: Offloads conversions via
  'g_spawn_command_line_async' to prevent UI freezing.
* Desktop Drag & Drop: Drop files from Thunar, Dolphin, PCManFM-QT, etc.
* Anti-Flashbang Theme Hook: Eight custom theme presets with a pre-inject
  loader to eliminate startup white screen flashes.
* Native Notifications: Alerts via 'notify-send' when conversions complete.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. UNDER THE HOOD
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* JS-to-C++ Bridge: Frontend extracts absolute file paths and sends only a
  lightweight metadata payload to the C++ controller, avoiding expensive
  browser-side canvas encoding.

* Intelligent Dispatcher: Automatically resolves output name conflicts and
  spawns independent child processes, for example:
  $ magick "/path/to/input.png" "/path/to/input_converted.webp"

* Resource Efficiency: Background processes utilize optimal CPU
  multithreading while maintaining close to 0% idle memory usage.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. USER SETTINGS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Configuration and active theme presets are automatically stored in:

  ~/.config/magicium/config.json

